Background and Objective. Illness specific stress plays an important part in the daily life of psoriatic patients. Until now for the measurement of relevant aspects of daily stress only the "Psoriasis Life Stress Inventory" (PLSI) of Gupta & Gupta exists; with the "Psoriasis-Alltagsstress-Inventar" (PAI), a German version of the PLSI is presented and its psychometric properties are discussed.  
